narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: In Tsyvinski's part, I gained several insights on the theoretical side of public finance. In Cormac's portion, I gained more insights into disability insurance, annuities, and life insurance.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: In the first part, we got exposed to many ideas, although at the cost of me feeling like we weren't spending enough time on most topics for me to feel very familiar with them. In the second part, the course covered several interesting topics related to Cormac's area of expertise. I think the material was interesting and relevant. I would maybe have liked to have seen more topics related to government spending on non-insurance areas, but public finance is a big topic and only a few things can be explored.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I audited this course, and I found it interesting. I would probably recommend at least auditing the course, as I found it interesting and often stimulating.
